        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 21 at 3:32PM MDT by NWS Boise ID</headline>
        <description>At 331 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Grasmere, or 32 miles north of Owyhee, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Areas of blowing dust possible. Minor
damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Blackstone Reservoir, Gedney Butte, Monument Butte, Twin Butte, and
Grasmere.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
